FBIS3-34925 "drnes032_n_94011" FBIS-NES-94-032 Document Type:Daily Report 16 Feb 1994 LEBANON Resistance Detonates Charges Under Patrols NC1402140494 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1230 GMT 14 Feb 94 NC1402140494 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] The Islamic Resistance announced that an explosive charge was detonated as an occupation patrol passed along the Shama' road in the security strip a few minutes after 0900 today. The occupation forces shelled Wadi al-Nafkhah and (Wadi Hinn) from their position in Tayr Harfa. The shelling continued intermittently until 1030. The Resistance also claimed the detonation of another charge at 1230 today as a patrol of the militia [South Lebanese Army, SLA] passed along the Shama'-Tayr Harfa road. The blast destroyed a red Mercedes 280 in which the militia's official in Tayr Harfa was riding. Last night, Resistance fighters attacked the Lahd [SLA] position in the central sector. A position of the Fijian contingent of the UN Interim Force in Lebanon in al-Mansuri was shelled from the militia [SLA] position in Jisr al-Hamra' at dawn today. The outskirts of Buyut al-Sayyid, al-Mansuri, and Majdal Zun came under shelling from the occupation forces' position in al-Bayyadah at dawn today. Israeli military planes overflew these areas and raked the nearby forests with machine-gun fire. Enemy planes overflew Zibqin, Kafra, Yatar, and Haris in dawn missions in which they fired flares. Israeli gunboats raked the area extending from al-Hamra' to al-Mansuri with machine-gun fire.
